columns.name: name
columns.description: A friendly name that identifies an API management backend.

columns.name: id
columns.description: Contains ID to identify an API management backend uniquely.

columns.name: url
columns.description: Runtime Url of the API management backend.

columns.name: type
columns.description: Resource type for API Management resource.

columns.name: protocol
columns.description: API management backend communication protocol. Possible values include: 'BackendProtocolHTTP', 'BackendProtocolSoap'.

columns.name: resource_id
columns.description: Management Uri of the Resource in External System. This url can be the Arm Resource Id of Logic Apps, Function Apps or Api Apps.

columns.name: properties
columns.description: The API management backend Properties contract.

columns.name: credentials
columns.description: The API management backend credentials contract properties.

columns.name: proxy
columns.description: The API management backend proxy contract properties.

columns.name: tls
columns.description: The API management backend TLS properties.

columns.name: service_name
columns.description: Name of the API management service.
